---
import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Yuxuan Wang" description="About Yuxuan Wang — Data Scientist specializing in clinical NLP and production ML">
	<div class="stack gap-20">
		<main class="wrapper about">
			<Hero
				title="About"
				tagline="Thanks for stopping by. Read below to learn more about myself and my background."
			>
				<img
					width="1553"
					height="873"
					src="/assets/at-work.jpg"
					alt="Yuxuan Wang at work"
				/>
			</Hero>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						Machine learning engineer focused on <strong>clinical NLP</strong> and <strong>medical coding automation</strong> — building
						systems where model decisions carry real consequences and accuracy is measured in
						<strong>healthcare outcomes</strong>, not just benchmarks.
					</p>
					<p>
						At <strong>XpertDox</strong>, I work across the full stack: redesigning data infrastructure, training and
						owning production models, and translating performance into the <strong>business metrics</strong> that actually
						matter to clinical and product stakeholders. The scope has grown from a narrow ICD classifier
						to a <strong>platform covering CPT, ICD, and billing across 2,000 codes</strong>.
					</p>
					<p>
						Before this, I worked across media and healthcare during my M.S. at NYU — forecasting at
						<strong>NBCUniversal</strong>, predictive modeling for <strong>non-invasive glucose monitoring</strong> — building the range
						that makes domain-specific depth more useful.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">How I Work</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						The longer I work in production ML, the more my definition of a good model has shifted —
						from one with strong metrics to one that actually <strong>fits the system it lives in</strong> and
						generates real value there. Those aren't always the same thing.
					</p>
					<p>
						In high-stakes domains, the most valuable use of a model is often not the obvious one —
						sometimes it's most useful not when it's <strong>confidently right</strong>, but when it <strong>quietly disagrees</strong>,
						flagging cases where learned patterns diverge from established rules for expert review.
						The technical work of building a good model is one problem; knowing what to do with it
						in a system built around <strong>human expertise</strong> is a different problem, and usually the more interesting one.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Outside Work</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						<strong>Hip-hop</strong> has held my attention for a long time — specifically the craft of it. Writing lyrics
						forces a kind of <strong>precision</strong> that's hard to find elsewhere: a complete idea, a distinct voice,
						and something worth saying, compressed into a tight structure. What draws me most is
						hip-hop as a <strong>platform</strong> — the way it lets you say something real and get it across to people
						who might not have encountered that perspective otherwise.
					</p>
					<p>
						I watch a lot of <strong>NBA</strong> and play <strong>basketball</strong> regularly. Team sports have a particular dynamic
						I find genuinely compelling — five people with different roles working toward something
						none of them could do alone. The combination of individual excellence and collective
						coordination, and the way <strong>trust</strong> has to be built in real time under pressure, is hard to replicate.
					</p>
					<p>
						<strong>Trading card games</strong> scratch a different itch: the intersection of favorite IPs and actual
						intellectual challenge. Deck-building is a <strong>design problem with constraints</strong>, and competitive
						play is applied <strong>game theory</strong>. The fact that it wraps all of that in something you genuinely
						care about makes it easy to go deep.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>

		<ContactCTA />
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.about {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 3.5rem;
	}

	img {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 1.5rem;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
	}

	section {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		color: var(--gray-200);
	}

	.section-title {
		grid-column-start: 1;
		font-size: var(--text-xl);
		color: var(--gray-0);
	}

	.content {
		grid-column: 2 / 4;
	}

	.content :global(a) {
		text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
		text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
		transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
	}

	.content :global(a:hover),
	.content :global(a:focus) {
		text-decoration-color: currentColor;
	}

	@media (min-width: 50em) {
		.about {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
		}

		.about > :global(:first-child) {
			grid-column-start: 2;
		}

		section {
			display: contents;
			font-size: var(--text-lg);
		}
	}
</style>
